pdpSummarySquareMileResearch: A Square Mile Fund Rating denotes a fund that is truly ‚Äúbest in class‚Äù. Put simply, a Square Mile Fund Rating is only given to a fund that they are prepared to recommend to clients.  Fund managers do not pay for the ratings; they cannot be purchased and are only achieved by the ‚Äúbest-in-class‚Äù funds.

The funds Square Mile recommend are each assigned a rating ‚Äì A, AA, AAA or R ‚Äì reflecting Square Mile‚Äôs conviction in each fund‚Äôs ability to deliver on expectations. These simple ratings are the result of exhaustive and detailed qualitative research, backed up by quantitative analysis. ‚ÄúAAA‚Äù represents the very highest level of conviction in a fund and its manager, and is a practical demonstration of their belief in the long-term consistent delivery of the fund‚Äôs objectives.

Square Mile‚Äôs team of investment research analysts also works to identify newer or untested funds or managers that have real potential to deliver their stated objectives. In these circumstances, Square Mile are not in a position to award a full fund rating, and therefore these funds are assigned a ‚ÄúPositive Prospects‚Äù rating. Over time, if these managers deliver to Square Mile‚Äôs expectations and achieve their expected outcome, Square Mile would expect them to progress to A, AA, AAA or R ratings.
